  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">INCLUSION II</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">(Vietnam):  .USAID &quot;INCLUSION&quot; project partners with three Vietnamese non-governmental organizations to implement a comprehensive intervention program aimed at improving the quality of life for persons with disabilities in provinces heavily sprayed with Agent Orange. ..With FY 2020 funding, the Center for Creative Initiatives in Health and Population (CCIHP) will work in Thua Thien Hue and Quang Tri provinces. Working through its sub-awardees, INCLUSION will build a multi-disciplinary rehabilitation service system and provide rehabilitation services to PWDs and home-based care and training to family members in nursing, nutrition and safety. The activity will also work to promote persons with disabilities&apos; social participation, build their independent living skills, and provide peer support and psychological support to family members. Disability policies and their implementation will be advanced through strengthening a number of efforts including revision of current policies, advocacy campaigns for the inclusion of anti-discrimination clauses, or development of new guidance for disabilities assistance. CCIHP will work with government agencies, civil society and the private sector to support the Journey to Self-reliance..This activity implements Congressional directives and supports the Administration&apos;s policy priority to address war legacies to advance the bilateral relationship. By providing direct services to PWDs, the activity contributes to the achievement of the Mission Objective for promoting greater social, economic, and political opportunities for the most vulnerable populations, including those suffering from war-related disabilities. The activity also supports the Journey to Self-Reliance by strengthening inclusion and participation of the vulnerable groups into society and building Vietnam&apos;s public-service delivery system.</narrative>
  </description>
